    <node id="1. Joe and Hill are pulling and straining on a rope that is tied to a raft of parampa logs in the middle of the river. They are trying to secure the raft to the muddy bank, as they have a limited amount of time before their ship lands at Landing City.&#10;2. The men are concerned about being late for their ship's landing because if they are, they may be crossed off the list, which implies that there is some sort of registration or quota system in place for travelers arriving on Midplanet. They need to secure the raft and make their way to Landing City in time to put in for their numbers on the list and avoid being excluded from traveling on the ship." />
