iloring outreach efforts accordingly could help attract a more diverse range of colonists.&#10;5. Finally, it may be helpful to engage in ongoing dialogue with potential colonists and gather feedback on their concerns and suggestions for improvement. This approach can help build trust and buy-in from potential colonists, and ensure that the colonization process is responsive to their needs and concerns.">
